	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001210_0001"/><!--pb/@n='89r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>18 Hart St</placeName>
<lb/><placeName>Bloomsbury Sq</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">8<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> Feby 1858 </p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>Would it be 
<lb/>possible to print 
<lb/>my little analysis 
<lb/>of the Sichuana 
<lb/>language for <hi rend="underline">private</hi>
<lb/>use with a margin 
<lb/>for future corrections 
<lb/>in a week from 
<lb/>this time? <choice><reg>A</reg><orig>a</orig></choice>nd 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001210_0002"/><!--pb/@n='89v'--> 
<lb/>if so at what cost? 
<lb/>It would be so 
<w>con-<lb break="no"/>venient</w> for my 
<lb/>studies that I beg 
<lb/>leave to trouble 
<lb/>you with the 
<lb/>question<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>Will you be 
<lb/>kind enough to 
<lb/>get BB Nautical 
<lb/>almanacks for 
<lb/>me. viz. 1858-9-60 
<lb/>Also the very latest 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001210_0003"/><!--pb/@n='90r'--> 
<lb/>edition of <persName>Thomson's</persName>
<lb/>Tables, Linear and 
<lb/>Lunary. I think it 
<lb/>was published within 
<lb/>the last few years. 
<lb/>The old one I have 
<lb/>already. </p>
<lb/><p>I may say 
<lb/>that you have 
<lb/>kindly put by 
<lb/>the analysis in 
<lb/>your drawer if 
<lb/>you <del type="strikethrough">wish</del> think right 
<lb/>to glance at its size<reg>.</reg>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001210_0004"/><!--pb/@n='90v'--> 
<lb/>And in case I forget 
<lb/>when with you 
<lb/>I would ask you 
<lb/>to leave out my 
<lb/>observation book 
<lb/>as I wish to take 
<lb/>it to the <placeName>Cape</placeName><reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>I shall call 
<lb/>tomorrow - perhaps 
<lb/>today but am 
<lb/>going up to 
<lb/><placeName>Wandsworth</placeName><reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>I am &amp;c </p>
<lb/><p><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p><addSpan spanTo="#p90v-01" hand="#hand01" place="marginleft"><!--addSpan/@place='left hand margin'--></addSpan>
<lb/><p><persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> L.</persName> found the essays in his own possession 
<lb/>&amp; the observations he had given to <persName>Arrowsmith</persName></p><anchor xml:id="p90v-01"/>
			
